# GitHub OAuth Setup Guide for SkillSphere

## Step 1 — Install backend packages

```bash
cd backend
npm install passport passport-github2 passport-google-oauth20 express-session
```

## Step 2 — Create GitHub OAuth App

1. Go to **https://github.com/settings/developers**
2. Click **"New OAuth App"**
3. Fill in:
   - **Application name:** `SkillSphere`
   - **Homepage URL:** `http://localhost:3000`
   - **Authorization callback URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/auth/github/callback`
4. Click **"Register application"**
5. Copy **Client ID** and **Client Secret**

## Step 3 — Add to backend/.env

```env
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here
GITHUB_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/auth/github/callback

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/auth/google/callback
```

## Step 4 — Update backend/server.js

Add these lines:

```js
const session        = require('express-session');
const passport       = require('passport');

// Session middleware (BEFORE passport)
app.use(session({
  secret:            process.env.SESSION_SECRET || 'skillsphere_session',
  resave:            false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  cookie:            { secure: false, maxAge: 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 },
}));

// Passport middleware
app.use(passport.initialize());

// GitHub OAuth routes
app.use('/api/auth/github', require('./routes/github.auth'));

// Google OAuth routes  
app.use('/api/auth/google', require('./routes/google.auth'));
```

## Step 5 — Copy backend files

| File | Path |
|---|---|
| `github.auth.js` | `backend/routes/github.auth.js` |
| `google.auth.js` | `backend/routes/google.auth.js` |

## Step 6 — Copy frontend files

| File | Path |
|---|---|
| `OAuthSuccess.js` | `src/pages/auth/OAuthSuccess.js` |
| `Login.js` | `src/pages/auth/Login.js` (GitHub button now works) |
| `App.js` | `src/App.js` (has /oauth-success route) |

## How the flow works

```
User clicks "GitHub" button
        ↓
/api/auth/github  (backend)
        ↓
GitHub login page opens
        ↓
User grants permission
        ↓
/api/auth/github/callback  (backend)
        ↓
Passport creates/finds user in MongoDB
        ↓
JWT token generated
        ↓
Redirect to /oauth-success?token=...&user=...
        ↓
OAuthSuccess.js saves token + user to Redux
        ↓
Navigate to /dashboard ✅
```

## For production

Change callback URLs in:
- GitHub OAuth App settings
- `.env` file

```env
GITHUB_CALLBACK_URL=https://yourdomain.com/api/auth/github/callback
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=https://yourdomain.com/api/auth/google/callback
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com
```